2) NVDA-IBMTTS-Driver anti-crash regex tables
   -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   The per-language regex tables under `sd_eloquence/src/filters/` (specifically
   `lang_global.c`, `lang_en.c`, `lang_es.c`, `lang_fr.c`, `lang_de.c`,
   `lang_pt.c`) are derived from the NVDA-IBMTTS-Driver project's
   `addon/synthDrivers/ibmeci.py` module, which is

       Copyright (C) 2009-2026 David CM (dhf360@gmail.com) and contributors

   and is released under the GNU General Public License version 2. Because
   those tables carry GPLv2 obligations forward, the entire `sd_eloquence/`
   subtree of this project is licensed under GPL-2.0-or-later (full text at
   `sd_eloquence/LICENSE.GPL`). All other parts of this project — including
   `macho2elf/`, `tools/`, `examples/`, `dist/`, and `docs/` — remain MIT
   per the license at the top of this file.

3) Apple ETI Eloquence dylibs (`vendor/tvOS-18.2/*.dylib`)
   -------------------------------------------------------------------------
   See the NOTE ON BINARY ARTIFACTS section above.
